edback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ddw1665702730320.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ddw1665702730320.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ddw1665702730320.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ddw1665702730320\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      slctenhance\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify that Uniface should not remove the cached SELECT statement until the next SELECT statement is different than the previous one.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ddw1665702730320__topic_d52514e1_d52515e1_d52516e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ddw1665702730320__p_d52517e1_d52518e1_d52519e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USYS$MSS_PARAMS = slctenhance: on | off</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ddw1665702730320__section_lwr_wth_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d679508e60\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ddw1665702730320__p_d52523e1_d52524e1_d52525e1\">Available only for the MSS U3.0 (and above)\n            connector</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ddw1665702730320__section_lzt_xth_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d679508e69\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ddw1665702730320__p_d52529e1_d52530e1_d52531e1\">The default setting of this option is\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>, which is the default Uniface behavior.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ddw1665702730320__p_d52532e1_d52533e1_d52534e1\">If set to <code class=\"ph codeph\">on</code>, Uniface does not remove\n            the SELECT statement cache until the next SELECT statement is different than the\n            previous one. If you have a one-to-many relationship situation where the number of\n            records in the outer and inner entities is very large, and you have ProcScript similar\n            to the following block, the default behavior of the SELECT cache mechanism can degrade\n            performance.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"ddw1665702730320__pre_kfm_yth_jcc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">retrieve\nSetOcc \"One-Entity\", 1\nwhile ($status &gt; 0)\n SetOcc \"Many-Entity\", 1\n while ($status &gt; 0)\n discard \"Many-Entity\"\n endwhile\n discard \"One-Entity\"\nendwhile\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"ddw1665702730320__note_rfm_yth_jcc\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You should use this option only when you have\n            ProcScript similar to the one described above.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526755\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526755\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "slctenhance Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 slctenhance Specify that Uniface should not remove the cached SELECT statement until the next SELECT statement is different than the previous one. USYS$MSS_PARAMS = slctenhance: on | off Use Available only for the MSS U3.0 (and above) connector Description The default setting of this option is off , which is the default Uniface behavior. If set to on , Uniface does not remove the SELECT statement cache until the next SELECT statement is different than the previous one. If you have a one-to-many relationship situation where the number of records in the outer and inner entities is very large, and you have ProcScript similar to the following block, the default behavior of the SELECT cache mechanism can degrade performance. retrieve SetOcc \"One-Entity\", 1 while ($status > 0) SetOcc \"Many-Entity\", 1 while ($status > 0) discard \"Many-Entity\" endwhile discard \"One-Entity\" endwhile Copy Note: You should use this option only when you have ProcScript similar to the one described above. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}